e-2 and the other cartservice pods, but all three show similar error characteristics.\n\n```json\n{\n  "detected_metric_keys": ["error_ratio", "client_error_ratio", "rrt_max"],\n  "affected_components": ["cartservice-0", "cartservice-1", "cartservice-2"],\n  "metric_summary": "cartservice shows high error ratios (21-23%) and elevated latency across all pods during fault window. cartservice-2 runs on aiops-k8s-03, but no cartservice pods run on aiops-k8s-04. Unable to verify node memory usage due to data access limitations.",\n  "time_series_analysis": {\n    "metric_name": "error_ratio",\n    "pattern": "elevated",\n    "critical_timestamps": ["2025-06-05T18:10:05Z to 2025-06-05T18:34:05Z"],\n    "value_change": "0.0% → 21-23%"\n  },\n  "contradictions": [\n    {\n      "evidence1": "All cartservice pods show similar error patterns regardless of node placement",\n      "evidence2": "Expected node-specific memory issues would affect only cartservice-2 on aiops-k8s-03",\n      "verification_needed": "Unable to access node memory metrics to confirm or rule out node-level issues"\n    }\n  ],\n  "next_verification": {\n    "action": "check_logs",\n    "reason": "Service-level errors across all cartservice pods suggest application or dependency issue rather than node memory problems",\n    "suggested_metrics": [],\n    "suggested_log_keywords": ["connection refused", "timeout", "memory", "OOM"]\n  }\n}\n```'}
